Citation.sTitle: Viscosity of aqueous solutions of 2-methoxyethanol, 2-ethoxyethanol, and ethanolamine
Citation.sAbstract: Viscosity (g) of (water+2-methoxyethanol), (water+2-ethoxyethanol), and (water+ ethanolamine) were measured precisely at the temperatures (303.15, 308.15, 313.15, 318.15, and 323.15) K covering the whole composition range. The viscosity deviations (Dg) from linearity based on mole fraction were calculated from the viscosity data and fitted to the Redlich-Kister equation. The Dg values are positive over the entire range of composition for (water+2-methoxyethanol) and (water+2-ethoxyethanol). Dg exhibits maximum at x?0.30 for (water+2-methoxyethanol), and at x?0.28 for (water+2-ethoxyethanol). While Dg values for (water+ethanolamine) are slightly negative up to x?0.24 with minimum at x?0.11, then become more positive over the rest composition with maximum at x?0.72. The Dg values, in all the cases, decrease with the increase in temperature.
